result.name: warrington-borough-council-councillor-expenses
result.notes: Councillors are paid an annual basic allowance to recognise the duties and responsibilities of their office, including attendance at Council meetings. Special Responsibility Allowances are paid to Councillors holding particular positions with extra responsibilities. Councillors are also reimbursed their reasonable travel and subsistence expenses incurred in attending meetings and carrying out other approved duties.
result.title: Warrington Borough Council councillor expenses
